## **POST /event/createEvent**
This endpoint is to list all Posts available inside of the DB.
<br>

### **Required Request Header**
```
{
    access_token :string
}
```


### **Required Request Body**
```
Sample:
===========
{
    "id": integer,
    "title": "string",
    "content": "text",
    "imageUrl": "string",
    "UserId":integer,
    "eventDate":date,
    "createdAt": "date",
    "updatedAt": "date"
}
```

### **Validation**
- Title cannot be empty
- content cannot be empty


### **Response Status**
```
Success
=======
200 OK

Error
=======
500 something happend with plis try again later
```

### **Response Body**
```
Successful sample:
====================
{
     message: `your event has been created` 
}
```
<br>

## **GET /event/:eventId**
This endpoint is to list all Posts available inside of the DB.
<br>

### **Required Request Header**
```
{
    access_token :string
}
```

### **Response Status**
```
Success
=======
200 OK

Error
=======
500 something happend with plis try again later
```

### **Response Body**
```
Successful sample:
====================
{
    "dataDetails": 
        {
        "id": integer,
        "title": "string",
        "content": "string",
        "eventDate": "date",
        "UserId": integer,
        "imageUrl": "string",
        "createdAt": "date",
        "updatedAt": "date"
        }, ...
    ]
}
```
<br>
